        "content": "### ${env:text} FishyStuff Dashboard\n\nEnvironment: **${env:text}** (`$env`)\n\nUse the health row first. Red tiles point at service errors, warning/error logs, trace errors, or host saturation. Dashboard links open env-scoped logs and Jaeger keeps traces searchable by `deployment.environment`.\n\nMetrics, logs, and spanmetrics are filtered by `env=\"$env\"`; beta data should not appear on production views. If prod shows zero hosts reporting logs, no prod telemetry has reached this stack in the selected window.",
